@node "INTRODUCTION" "Welcome.."

                               @{b}@{u}INTRODUCTION@{ub}@{uu}


Thank you for buying the Blitz Support Suite, we hope you find the
REDBlitzLibs as much use to you as they are to ourselves...

Blitz Basic is probably the best language for the Amiga when it comes
to features and ease of use. However, a few features are missing from
its command set, and this is where you need the REDBlitzLibs.

The REDBlitzLibs used to be known as the RIBlitzLibs, but now that we
are set up as a professional development house, we decided to change
the RI to RED. The REDBlitzLibs features many new commands since the
public release of RIBlitzLibs and also features many bug-fixes.
@endnode

@node "REQUIREMENTS" "What do I need?"

                                 @{b}@{u}REQUIREMENTS@{ub}@{uu}

This version of REDBlitzLibs requires an Amiga with at least Kickstart
1.3 ROMs and 1MB RAM. In addition, you will require Blitz Basic 2 V1.7
or higher. Many commands require higher versions of Kickstart, and most
STRING returning functions (return and pass strings) require Blitz
Basic 2 V1.9 or higherą.

Some commands also require the AGA chipsetą.

ą - The documentation for the library/command will tell you of any
special
    requirements.

@endnode

