@node "use" "How to use"
Here you can add all your thousands of functions and can find them
Make files like  myfuncs.bb2
Add the function or functions you want in a macro.
This allow you to build a .res file.This file can be as large you want
only the functions you want are copied in your source.

The instructionhelp can list you this macros.Doubleclicking then open
the amigaguide in Blitz2:redhelp/usermacros.guide.Here you can add docu if you wish

Example: your myfunc.bb2 contain this:

macro myfunc
statement myfunc{rastport,x,y}

blah bla

end statement
end macro

your Code then contain somewhere before the first call a
!myfunc
to add the function to the code
Now you have included the function to the code and you can work as before




@endnode
